{"_id":"MmRjZWM4NGViNjAw","name":"1. Entrance Chamber","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":0,"pages":[{"name":"1. Entrance Chamber","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-001a2179-7fff-58c8-626b-423d62140b56\"></span></p><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left:0pt\"><br /></div><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><p><i><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">A set of double doors opens into the first chamber of the tomb is a large rectangular chamber, the final resting place of the first 8 members of the </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b>Silverkrag Clan</b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> to settle in the area. An array of sarcophagi are arranged in the chamber, made of granite and carved in fine likenesses of the deceased. The walls and floors of the tomb are sturdy plain granite.</span></i></p></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span>Blade Trap (1A)</span></h4><p style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">There is another set of double doors opposite the entrance, which are slightly ajar and upon investigation appear damaged. In front of the doors, there lies a dead</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> A DC 12 Medicine check reveals several small puncture wounds through the thorax as the cause of death. Or, a DC 14 Investigation check means that the PC finds the holes in the ceiling, from which spring an array of 9 long thin blades, piercing anyone who steps on the pressure plate which the corpse is currently sitting on. Success on either check grants advantage on the other check, if made subsequently. </span></span></p><p style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><br /></span></span></p><h4 style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Treasure.</span></h4><p style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif;background-color:\">If the players ransack the room, they can find some jewelry; four rings worth 5 gp each.</span><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"X5xTZoMnsxC5SXHj","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"MzZhOGU5ZTMyNGVl","name":"4. Fancy Burial Chamber","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":3,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":30000,"pages":[{"name":"4. Fancy Burial Chamber","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><br /></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-f8f6274f-7fff-192c-2af1-f9743e4a2cdf\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><i>This larger burial chamber is newer than the previous sections, with better workmanship (or workdwarfship?) clearly evident. The center of the room contains two sarcophagi facing one another. </i></span></span><br /></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h4><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-60d26802-7fff-7dd0-f4b6-ee1bdb4c80e3\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Blade Trap (4A).</span></span></h4><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-60d26802-7fff-7dd0-f4b6-ee1bdb4c80e3\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Opening the door to the chamber will cause a blade to jut forth from the side; any creature doing so must make a DC 13 Dexterity Saving Throw or take 2d4 slashing damage.</span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The chamber contains one @Actor[MTZkNjdlNjY1NmVm]{Ankheg} </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">and one @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}.</span></p><h4><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-60d26802-7fff-7dd0-f4b6-ee1bdb4c80e3\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-4ce88bd6-7fff-b32d-eb6d-85a6daa94c7c\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Treasure.</span></span></span></span></h4><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If the players ransack the room, they can find some jewelry; a ring worth 50 gp, a necklace worth 25 gp, and a @JournalEntry[OTY5YWU4N2MzYzhl]{Cursed Dwarven Battle Hammer}</span></p></section>"},"_id":"7176R9yxeY3AwTfv","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"N2M0MzQ2ZGE4MDVl","name":"3. Ochre Jelly Chamber","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":2,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":20000,"pages":[{"name":"3. Ochre Jelly Chamber","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><br /></p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Unlike all the other doors on this level, the door to this room is undisturbed, and a player giving the door a closer look will immediately notice that the edges of the door are also sealed with wax. </span></p><p><br /></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><i><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-6ddf9f97-7fff-796e-0345-e605014912c5\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">As you crack the wax seal and breach the door, you reveal a large burial chamber; it was clearly originally finely done, however the walls and sarcophagi have been ruined by a thick viscous substance, etching and pitting their surfaces. Reacting to the movement of the door opening, the substance flows and oozes and coalesces. </span></span><br /></i></td></tr></tbody></table><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-c65c523c-7fff-b6e3-3d46-5705c7ed09c9\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The players are attacked by an @Actor[OGRlNzhhNDE4MjI3]{Ochre Jelly}, </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">which had been sealed within, if they choose to open the door. If they break the wax seal on the door but don’t open it, then the Jelly may instead be waiting for them on their way out of the tomb. </span></span><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"EqyfQKw1Mrxia7eg","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"NDIzM2JhYjY2MTJm","name":"Wind Fan","folder":"Y2E4NmM3NWIyN2Yx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":3,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":30000,"pages":[{"name":"Figure: Wind Fan","type":"image","src":"worlds/excessive-excavations/journal/003_-_Magic_Items/003_-_Wind_Fan/avatar_1.png","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"_id":"v4ItNQkBS6Hgao8p","image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Wind Fan","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><i>Adventuring gear (wonderous item), uncommon</i></p><p>While holding this fan, you can use an action to cast the <a class=\"userscript-autolink\" href=\"https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Gust%20of%20Wind#h-Gust%20of%20Wind\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted rgb( 65 , 143 , 222 )\">Gust of Wind</a> spell (save DC 13) from it. Once used, the fan shouldn't be used again until the next dawn. Each time it is used again before then, it has a cumulative 20 percent chance of not working and tearing into useless, nonmagical tatters.<br /></p>"},"_id":"9N5qR42t6iuolYwF","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"ODI2MDQzZmM4NmU0","name":"Adventure Resolution","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":8,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":80000,"pages":[{"name":"Adventure Resolution","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Each player should be awarded with 900 XP for clearing out the Ankheg infestation, and an additional 100 XP if they dealt with the optional Ochre Jelly. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Upon returning, </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Baroness Hamilda Silverkrag</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> will happily reward the players with the agreed upon sum (200 gp, with a possible additional 25 gp if the players had asked about the hazards in the tomb and knew about the Ochre Jelly and killed it). </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">In the event that the players looted the tomb, the Barsoness will not immediately find out, but within a few days of repair, it will be obvious that there are relics missing and that the players were the only likely culprits. They will be branded as grave robbers, and a warrant issued for their arrest in the Fiefdom. This only occurs if they keep the items; some player groups might loot items, encounter the ghosts and after the fight realize that maybe they shouldn’t have been looting the place, and return the items. </span></p><h3 style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Beyond the Tomb </span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The adventuring group either made an ally or an enemy through the course of the adventure, depending on whether or not they chose to loot the tomb. For players who did loot the tomb, further adventures can tie into this plot line by having the group need to deal with bounty hunters sent after them, or even staging a trial. This could provide a good opportunity to provide a plot hook for a follow on adventure, whereby the group could be sentenced to absolve their crimes by performing some public service, such as slaying a dangerous monster. Groups that didn’t loot the tomb, on the other hand, will be seen as trustworthy by the Baroness, and could be hired by her again in order to perform various tasks, be it in her capacity as head of the mining company, or her new capacity as ruler of the Fiefdom. This could prove to be a very lucrative arrangement. </span></p><div><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"><br /></span></div></section>"},"_id":"3jd5tUQ4MwWv148F","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"OGY1OTkwOTRkNGUy","name":"Background and Running the Adventure","folder":"M2JjZDQ1MWVmNmNh","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":10000,"pages":[{"name":"Background and Running the Adventure","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">This is a 5e adventure which is optimized for a party of four 3rd level characters. It is expected that it will take most groups approximately 4 hours to complete.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><br /></span></p><h2 style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\">Background</h2><p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">A group of miners were expanding a tomb, adding a new level beneath the existing catacombs. This tomb, the ancestral burial chambers for the </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Silverkrag</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i> </i></b>family already houses several generations of dwarves, with the tomb being added to over time, with the chambers getting more ornate as the family amassed wealth. The latest level was built to be the resting place of </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Killiam</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, built by his daughter </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Hamilda</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, who had recently been appointed to the nobility. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt\"><br /></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The excavations however came close to a lair of </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b>Ankheg</b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, who burrowed into the burial chamber and attacked the miners. It’s the PC’s job to clear out the tomb of any hostiles. Or maybe they just heard about it happening and decided it was an opportunity to raid the place. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt\"><br /></p><h2 style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Running the Adventure</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">This adventure focuses on the ancestral tomb of an up-and-coming dwarven clan, whose fortunes have been on the rise over the generations. Centuries ago they struck out on their own, moving from their homeland in search of prosperity, and have since found it. This adventure location can fit into any urban, suburban, or rural area in your game world. The </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b>Silverkrag</b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> family have been making their fortune in the mining industry, though you can adapt the source of their prosperity if mining doesn’t suit the local economy or resources in your game world. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt\"><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">While excavations on the next level of the tomb were interrupted, the timeline is growing somewhat critical, as </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Killiam’s</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i> </i></b>health is rapidly deteriorating, and </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Hamilda </i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">is strongly motivated to complete the tomb on time for her father’s funeral. </span><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"5aTL8e4KPxut6kZF","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"OTI0YTdlOWNhZTYx","name":"Adjusting Encounter Difficulty","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":7,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":70000,"pages":[{"name":"Adjusting Encounter Difficulty","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-ec6ecd0b-7fff-a442-d99e-c5fc663bcd8a\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">This adventure can be rebalanced for groups of different level and size by increasing or decreasing the DCs of any ability checks or saves; adjusting up or down one for every two levels. If the players are below level 4, the </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><i>Summon Defenders</i></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> feature of the @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen} </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">should recharge only on a roll of 6. Adjusting difficulty down can be accomplished by removing some @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, and/or downgrading a @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter} </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">to an @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">. Conversely, difficulty can be increased by upgrading workers to spitters, regular @Actor[MTZkNjdlNjY1NmVm]{Ankheg} </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">to @Actor[MDFlNjkyMGE0NmIx]{Ankheg Tank}s</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, and adding more @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}s and @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}s</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-5ba002c9-7fff-694e-836e-9c0fd59c8e87\"><br /></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If your adventurers dealt with the Ankheg infestation handily, you may wish to consider having them encounter a group of grave robbers, taking advantage of the disturbance. They can have an ambush set for the group in the entrance chamber of the tomb. </span></p></span></h2></section>"},"_id":"yNwZCv92UNI7P405","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"OTY5YWU4N2MzYzhl","name":"Cursed Dwarven Battle Hammer","folder":"Y2E4NmM3NWIyN2Yx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":10000,"pages":[{"name":"Figure: Cursed Dwarven Battle Hammer","type":"image","src":"worlds/excessive-excavations/journal/003_-_Magic_Items/001_-_Cursed_Dwarven_Battle_Hammer/avatar_1.png","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"_id":"OvpnyOHFl9QrFbiq","image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Cursed Dwarven Battle Hammer","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">melee weapon, (martial, warhammer) </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">This battle hammer is surprisingly light. It is a one-handed weapon, with the finesse property. Players can use this weapon easily even if not proficient in martial weapons. On a hit, it does 2d4 bludgeoning damage (does not count as magic weapon damage).</span></p><p><b style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-933629ce-7fff-4b35-adfa-aaaa0d0ec51c\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">Cursed: In doing so, they lose proficiency in any other weapons. As the saying goes, if all you have is a hammer, everything looks like a nail; gradually over time the character increasingly views all problems as “nails” to be “hammered down”. </span></p><p><br /><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );background-color:transparent;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">If the curse is removed, its properties revert to a standard <i>w</i></span><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );background-color:transparent;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"><i>arhammer</i></span><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );background-color:transparent;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">.</span><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"CKN3rSSuv6PeSv80","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"OTYxOTU5OTdjYzcz","name":"Goggles of Night","folder":"Y2E4NmM3NWIyN2Yx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":2,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":20000,"pages":[{"name":"Figure: Goggles of Night","type":"image","src":"worlds/excessive-excavations/journal/003_-_Magic_Items/002_-_Goggles_of_Night/avatar_1.png","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"_id":"too795qvsN2xfq9W","image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Goggles of Night","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><i>Wonderous item, uncommon</i></p><p>While wearing these dark lenses, you have darkvision out to a range of 60 feet. If you already have darkvision, wearing the googles increases its range by 60 feet.</p>"},"_id":"OcGkerRWrfQkSbf5","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"YTM0NDBhYzY4NTI4","name":"Getting Setup","folder":"M2JjZDQ1MWVmNmNh","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":0,"pages":[{"name":"Getting Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Welcome!</p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\">This module is fully set up to run with your adventurers,\njust use the area guides found under the Areas/Rooms folder. Each area number is\nindicated on the map for easy reference. Within each area write-up, the needed\nmonsters are hyperlinked as well and have been prepopulated on the different\nmaps.</p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\">A full PDF of the adventure can be found at the bottom of\nthe Journal column if needed.</p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\">Dynamic Lighting: This module is set up for use with Dynamic\nLighting. To set up your player’s tokens for them map, follow the steps below:</p><ol><li>Double Click on a Player’s token.</li><li>Select the Dynamic Lighting tab under Token Settings.</li><li>Under Token Vision, flip on Vision.</li></ol><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\">This process needed to be done for each of your player’s\ntokens.</p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\"><span>Thank you for purchasing this adventure.</span></p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\"></p>\n\n<p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\">Happy gaming!</p>\n\n<p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\"> </p>\n\n<p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\">One-Eyed Werebear Staff</p><p class=\"userscript-MsoNormal\"></p></section>"},"_id":"nwtSEDGB5rGyf1AV","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"YTQwODQzNDZlYWIz","name":"6. Ongoing Excavations","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":5,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":50000,"pages":[{"name":"6. Ongoing Excavations","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><br /></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-9d4b1c65-7fff-a066-5dc3-b10c1d7a06a7\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin:0pt 9.09449pt 0pt 7.08661pt\"><i><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">You head down the set of stairs, rough hewn out of the stone, and descend into the darkness. This set of stairs continues down further than the previous ones, eventually ending in a landing. You see an unfinished chamber, intended to be the final resting place of </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b>Killiam Silverkrag</b>.</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> The overall design of the chamber is evident, with a high domed ceiling supported by thick four pillars, surrounding a dias raised in the center. </span></i></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin:0pt 9.09449pt 0pt 7.08661pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><i>The east portion of the chamber is still being carved out, with scaffolding set up to allow the carving out of the higher portions of the current rock wall. Blood is splattered on the wall and floor in that section, and there is a myriad of hastily discarded digging tools.</i></span></p><div><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 102 , 102 , 102 );background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"><br /></span></div></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Within the chamber are one @Actor[MDFlNjkyMGE0NmIx]{Ankheg Tank}, three @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}s, and two @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}s</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> The Ankheg have been busy in this chamber as well, with a number of holes dug into the rock walls and floor.</span></p><p style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"></p><h4><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Gas Vents (5A). </span></h4><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span>Some of the holes on the floor are venting a gas, imparting a hazy sheen in the air to a 15 ft  x 15 ft area centered around the points indicated on the map. Any creature who enters into that space or starts their turn in that space will feel woozy, and will have to make a DC 13 Constitution Saving Throw. If they fail, then on their turn their movement speed is reduced to half of its normal amount, they can only make one action or one bonus action (not both), if they are holding concentration on a spell, it drops, any attacks are made at disadvantage, and any other creature that needs to make a save based upon a spell or ability triggered by the woozy makes that save at advantage. This gas is also flammable, and if any fire source enters the space, or any effect imparting fire or lightning damage enters or crosses the space, the gas explodes and any creatures within the gas must make a DC 13 Dexterity Saving Throw or take 3d6 fire damage (half damage if they make the save). The hole at the centre of the gas vent also causes that space to be difficult terrain. </span></span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The tunnel in the southeast corner of the chamber was dug out by the Ankheg. At the end of the tunnel, the hole angles sharply downward. Players can climb downward by making a DC 12 Athletics check to avoid falling. If they fail the check, they slip and bounce off the angled walls of the tunnel before landing at the bottom, taking 2d6 bludgeoning damage. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-dba1b3e1-7fff-40a6-b6c5-a90b62390a64\"></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If they somehow secure or hold a rope from the top and use it to climb, the Athletics check is made at advantage. Please note the tunnel is smooth enough that there’s no obvious point in the small chamber at the top to which a rope could be tied. Clever players may think of a way to do so, such as with the use of the discarded digging tools in the burial chamber to carve out an anchor point. </span></p></section>"},"_id":"SkZnqGVzBzbEuaFN","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"YjZkZjBlODgxMTBl","name":"7. Ankheg Queen's Nest","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":6,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":60000,"pages":[{"name":"7. Ankheg Queen's Nest","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><br /></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-c2bb0cf6-7fff-e5c6-aa37-81826a6fee21\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><i>You arrive at the bottom of the tunnel, opening into a chamber,  with a tunnel around the corner. As you arrive, an Ankheg Worker notices you, and begins burrowing.</i></span></span><br /></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen}'s </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Nest is hollowed out from a layer of mostly clay-like soil. The first room has one</span><span> </span><span>@Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker} </span><span>who notices the players arriving, and starts burrowing through the wall to the south. If the players kill it in time (without making too much noise), they have a chance to get the jump on the Queen. Otherwise, she is prepared and waiting on them. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen}'s chamber to the south has the Queen (initially in the back corner of the acid pool), and three @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}s </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">and three @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}s</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">. She is surrounded by a pool of acid. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"></p><h4><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Acid Pool.</span></h4><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The main chamber of the</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif\"> @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen}'s </span>Nest features a large pool of a thick sickly green liquid. Any creature which starts its turn in the pool takes 1d4 acid damage, as does any creature which ends its turn in the pool. Any creature which falls prone in the pool immediately takes 2d4 acid damage. </span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"></p><h4><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Battle Plans.</span></h4><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif\"> @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen} </span>will keep her distance for as long as she has others defending her, and will focus on calling forth defenders if she can, or lobbing acid blasts if her </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Summon Defenders</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> feature is recharging. Any</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif\"> @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}</span> will attempt to grapple and drag enemies into the pool of acid.</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif\"> @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}</span> </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">will concentrate their acid globules on whichever member of the party is the most obvious threat to the</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif\"> @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen}. </span>No Ankheg</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">will use their reactions to make attacks of opportunity, as that reaction will instead be used for the “Defend the Queen!” feature, where the creatures dive in front of any ranged attack in order to take the hit instead of the</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif\"> @Actor[YTA3Mjg2MmVlY2Qy]{Ankheg Queen}.</span>  </span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"></p><h4><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Treasure.</span></h4><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Sunk into the acid are a number of shiny jewels and coins that have resisted the acid's effects over the years. Players which search the pool find 2d6 gems worth 50 gp each, 2d6 x 10 gp, and 1d4 pp. As well, there is a set of @JournalEntry[OTYxOTU5OTdjYzcz]{Goggles of Night} </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">(if all your players already have darkvision, you might want to consider swapping this out for another suitable uncommon magic item). Around eggs a thicker, the party can also discover @JournalEntry[ZGNhZTIzMTE0YmU2]{Ankheg Royal Jelly}, which can be harvested.</span></p><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Exactly how they go about searching the pool or extracting the @JournalEntry[ZGNhZTIzMTE0YmU2]{Ankheg Royal Jelly} should determine whether or not you decide they take acid damage in the process. </span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-a992b9bf-7fff-51bf-4f7e-01b9a0e7b92f\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Please note that taking the treasure from this area does not count as looting the tomb, either for the purposes of angering the ghosts in area 5, or later on for determination of whether or not </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Baroness Hamilda Silverkrag</i></b> </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">decides to “deal” with the people who stole from her family’s graves</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> </span></span><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"8IQFk3HjSUtxpcHB","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"YmNjOTViNTJkYTcy","name":"One-Eyed Werebear Gaming","folder":null,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":4,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":40000,"pages":[{"name":"Figure: One-Eyed Werebear Gaming","type":"image","src":"worlds/excessive-excavations/journal/004_-_One-Eyed_Werebear_Gaming/avatar.png","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"_id":"g73ROHpDO0qeBpGO","image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"One-Eyed Werebear Gaming","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:\">One-Eyed Werebear Gaming is a collaboration between friends who enjoy role playing games and want to share our passion and creativity with you. We are Canadians who love adventure, storytelling and creation, particularly through DnD 5e. It is our joy to provide adventures, tools and content for busy GMs and players for your own awesome campaigns!</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:\"><br /></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:\">Sign up for our newsletter to get new creatures, magic items, maps, and more! <a href=\"https://1ewb.eo.page/newsletter\">newsletter.oneeyedwerebear.com</a></span><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"7AKepCkQaWGNUlvt","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":2},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1670699147049,"lastModifiedBy":"NjllNjg2MmJiMmVk"}}
{"_id":"ZGNhMTJmMDgxYjFh","name":"2. Individual Burial Chambers","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":10000,"pages":[{"name":"2. Individual Burial Chambers","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><br /></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-c89264cd-7fff-5acf-ebcb-bcd0057cd2de\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><i>The double doors open up into a long passage-way. Behind you, daylight streams into the Entrance Chamber, penetrating far enough past you that you can see a long corridor, with some doors set into the passage, as well as a cross-corridor with passages leading off into either side. </i></span></span><br /></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">T</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">his section of the tomb contains a series of smaller burial chambers, each containing the remains of either an individual, or a married couple. All the doors, with the exception of the door leading to area 3, are damaged and ajar. There are two @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}s and two @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}s</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> within this area, who are engaged in exploring the space, and disturbing the tomb. When the players arrive, place one @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker} </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">within the first chamber to the left, and the remainder of the creatures within the branching tunnels to either side</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><h4 style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Alarm Trap (2A)</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span></h4><p style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If a creature or player comes within 2 feet of a rune placed in the center of this space, the rune flashes, issuing an audible alarm akin to the ringing of a gong, and an announcement in Dwarven shouting “Grave Robbers!”. Players investigating the area can notice the rune with a DC 12 Investigation or Perception check, and can avoid triggering the rune if they make a DC 13 Acrobatics check to jump around the space in which the rune would be triggered. If triggered, the alarm alerts all the Ankheg in area 2. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><h4 style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Fire Dart Trap (2B)</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span></h4><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If the door is opened, a dart  of fire shoots forth from a hole above the sole sarcophagus in the room. Roll a magical range attack against the first creature in front of the door, with a +3 bonus against their AC. On a hit, they take 2d6 fire damage. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><h4 style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Gas Trap (2C)</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span></h4><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Any creature which steps on a pressure plate in this junction will trigger a gas cloud. All creatures within 5 feet of the trap must make a DC 13 Constitution Saving Throw or take 2d4 poison damage. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><h4><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Treasure. </span></h4><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If the players ransack the tombs, they can find some jewelry; four rings worth 5 gp each, and a necklace worth 10 gp.</span><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"uVOQ1AIvjw94mYKS","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"ZGNhZTIzMTE0YmU2","name":"Ankheg Royal Jelly","folder":"Y2E4NmM3NWIyN2Yx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":0,"pages":[{"name":"Figure: Ankheg Royal Jelly","type":"image","src":"worlds/excessive-excavations/journal/003_-_Magic_Items/000_-_Ankheg_Royal_Jelly/avatar_1.png","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"_id":"rdRuko8uXtsbR0V4","image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Ankheg Royal Jelly","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><i>Wondrous item, rare</i><br /></p><p>The Ankheg’s Royal Jelly is a bitter-sweet <span>golden jelly, found in carved alcoves lining the </span><span>Ankheg Queen’s lair.</span></p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p>If the players decide to try eating some, roll a d20 to determine the effect on the PC. Each PC can eat a maximum of 3 doses of the jelly. </p><p>Unless otherwise mentioned, all effects listed are permanent. Should the players decide to harvest the jelly, it loses its potency somewhat, and does not result in a roll on the table.</p><p>The harvested jelly is a delicacy, and a  maximum of 5 lbs collected can be sold for 50 gp, or used as a food source which can provide sustenance to an average person for 30 days. Jelly harvested does not spoil unless mixed with other food.</p><h2>Royal Jelly Effects Table</h2><p><br /></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><p><b>1</b> - <span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-51b9593a-7fff-faf8-aab5-e6da105eb234\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Take 3d6 acid damage.</span></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>2</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">Heal 20 hit points.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>3</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent\">Gain the ability to, as an action, shoot a line of acid that is 20 ft long and 5 ft wide. Each creature in the line must make a DC </span><span style=\"background-color:transparent\">13 Dexterity saving throw, taking 2d4 (5) acid damage, on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful save.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>4</b> - <span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-3f32b46b-7fff-4c0a-5805-60bffe0505e6\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Gain a single free use of the Charm Monster spell, which can only target insect-like monstrosities or beasts. The target automatically fails any saving throw, however the effect only lasts until the end of the PC's next turn. After this effect ends, the target becomes enraged and focuses exclusively on the PC, gaining advantage on its first attack against the PC.</span></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>5</b> - <span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-b1dc0483-7fff-5085-63fa-458f59cb9d24\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">A strange feeling of purity passes through the PC’s body as any diseases or negative conditions affecting them are removed. The PC becomes immune to disease and poison for the next seven days.</span></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>6</b> - <span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-bf0127c2-7fff-cd03-80de-5a1d077fd679\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Become part of the Ankheg hive. PC receives and acts upon the orders of the swarm, obeying the will of the Ankheg Queen (if still alive). If all the Ankheg in the hive are dead, the PC will use their first action to enact the \"Summon defenders” ability from the Ankheg Queen's stat block. This effect lasts for 1d4 hours. </span></span></p><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-bf0127c2-7fff-cd03-80de-5a1d077fd679\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The PC can make a DC 14 Charisma saving throw to throw off this effect every 10 minutes. Other members of the adventuring party will be viewed as enemies.</span></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>7</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The Royal Jelly causes extreme diarrhea. For the next 1d6 days, every time the PC takes a long rest, they must make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw; if they fail, instead of losing a level of exhaustion, they gain a level of exhaustion.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>8</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC's skin begins to harden, growing some chitinous plates. They gain a +1 bonus to their AC, but must also reduce their Charisma score by 1 point.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>9</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">During their next long rest, the PC grows 10% larger in height and gains 20% more weight.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>10</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC gains resistance to acid damage.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>11</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC becomes poisoned until their next long rest.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>12</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC does not need to eat, drink, or breathe for the next 2 days.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>13</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC gains the ability to communicate telepathically with Ankheg, and other hive insects and other animals. Also, the PC loses the ability to communicate in one language they are proficient in (player's choice, no effect occurs if this would cause them to forget all languages they know).</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>14</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">On any Persuasion or Deception ability check made by the PC, a roll below 9 is treated as if a 10 was rolled instead.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>15</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">Make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw. On a success, the PC gains 5 HP. On a failure, they vomit up the Royal Jelly, become nauseated and cannot attempt to eat anything until the end of their next long rest.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>16</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC g</span><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-9f9f7fe9-7fff-015d-e936-b9a77b5acf5e\" style=\"background-color:transparent\">ains tremorsense to a range of 30 ft.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>17</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC raises a random ability score by 1.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>18</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC gains advantage on all saving throws versus poison or acid effects.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>19</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The PC becomes unreasonably confident for the next 7 days.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>20</b> - <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:&quot;proxima nova&quot; , , , &quot;blinkmacsystemfont&quot; , &quot;segoe ui&quot; , &quot;roboto&quot; , , &quot;ubuntu&quot; , &quot;cantarell&quot; , &quot;helvetica neue&quot; , sans-serif\">The Royal Jelly is extremely spicy. The PC does not gain the benefits of their next long rest, due to the fact that it's also extremely spicy on its way out.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><br /></p></section>"},"_id":"U9pODDEDawBXE554","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"ZGUzOTMxNjgzOTgw","name":"5. Ornate Burial Chamber","folder":"YWFhZGI1YzhkNTkx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":4,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":40000,"pages":[{"name":"5. Ornate Burial Chamber","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><i><br /></i></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><i><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-14e0da3b-7fff-b306-7c38-582694bffe11\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">One level down the stairs, the landing opens into a burial chamber which is even more ornate and finely decorated than the ones on the level above. Finely detailed carvings celebrating the accomplishments of the deceased line the walls. Two large sarcophagi in the centre of the room are undisturbed. Scattered throughout the room are several corpses of various Ankheg castes.</span></span><br /></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The dead Ankheg on the floor (four @Actor[MGQyOGYyNmYyYjBk]{Ankheg Spitter}s, three @Actor[NGFlMDgwYzFjNGFi]{Ankheg Worker}s, and one @Actor[MTZkNjdlNjY1NmVm]{Ankheg}) </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">do not have an immediately apparent cause of death. When the party enters the chamber, a pair of dwarven spirits pops out from the sarcophagi. Both look much like they did in life, albeit translucent. One is a burly male dwarf, holding a mining pick in his hand, dressed in sturdy leather breeches and a wool top. The female dwarven spirit is dressed in a fine dress, and bears a strong resemblance to </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Baroness Hamilda Silverkrag</span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Mechanically speaking, the spirits are treated as a @Actor[MTVhNTc3OTFlNzZl]{Ghost} and a @Actor[NDU1NmMwNTk2ZmQy]{Shadow}.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The spirits begin shouting at the group, first in dwarven and then switching to common if the group indicates that they don’t speak dwarven. </span></p><table class=\"userscript-table userscript-table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-96e49891-7fff-5f27-de59-2dc4bdd2ef44\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><i>“Grave robbers will not be tolerated! You and your ilk will share the same fate as these vermin!” the female dwarf shouts, as both start to glide towards you, wildly gesturing in the direction of the desiccated remains of the many Ankheg littering the floor of the burial chamber. </i></span></span><br /></td></tr></tbody></table><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The spirits can be talked down. If the players did not loot any valuables from the tombs in the level above, the two spirits can be convinced that they had been sent on behalf of </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Hamilda Silverkrag</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, and that they intend to clear the tomb of the vermin infestation, and restore them to peace. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Convincing the spirits of their sincerity will require a DC 13 Persuasion check, or a DC 16 Deception check if they’re lying about having been sent by </span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i>Hamilda</i></b></span><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">. If the player who is making the Persuasion check speaks Dwarven, the check is made with advantage. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">If the players had looted any valuables from the tomb, the spirits sense it and immediately attack, and likewise do so if the group fails to convince the spirits that they were sent by the clan in order to clear the tomb. </span></p><h4 style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:15pt;margin-bottom:15pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Treasure.<br /></span><p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline;font-weight:normal\">If the players ransack the chamber, they can find a <span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:;color:rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 );vertical-align:baseline\">Wind Fan</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;helvetica neue&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , &quot;arial&quot; , sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:;color:rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 );vertical-align:baseline\">, a necklace worth 25 gp, and a ring worth 100 gp. The ring is cursed; anyone who touches it is haunted by nightmares and must make a DC 13 Charisma Saving Throw at the end of every long rest, otherwise they only gain the benefits of a short rest instead of a long rest.</span></span></p></h4></section>"},"_id":"xZoChy5R1aM4Uvnk","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
{"_id":"ZTRhYWEzZTVkMGRj","name":"Adventure Hooks","folder":"M2JjZDQ1MWVmNmNh","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":2,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":20000,"pages":[{"name":"Adventure Hooks","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left:14.173228346456689pt\"><table style=\"border:none;border-collapse:collapse\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:0pt\"><td style=\"border-left:solid #000000 1pt;border-right:solid #000000 1pt;border-bottom:solid #000000 1pt;border-top:solid #000000 1pt;vertical-align:top;padding:5pt 5pt 5pt 5pt;overflow:hidden\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-left:7.086614173228355pt;margin-right:9.094488188976399pt;text-align:justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-6de7518c-7fff-46b5-38c6-67603af13f9b\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 102 , 102 , 102 );background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A notice is posted at the local inn: Adventurers Wanted to deal with pest removal. Serious inquiries only at Silverkrag Mining Company. Reward, 200 gp. </span></span><br /></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-e7bc8520-7fff-69d2-dc3c-397f40f624d0\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );background-color:transparent;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">If the players inquire at the mining company (or whichever industry you decide the </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"><b>Silverkrag Clan</b> </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );background-color:transparent;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">is working within), they are led to the office of the company chairdwarf and newly appointed Baroness of &lt;insert local county&gt;.</span></span><br /></p><p><b style=\"font-weight:normal\"><br /></b></p><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left:4.5pt\"><table style=\"border:none;border-collapse:collapse\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:0pt\"><td style=\"border-left:solid #000000 1pt;border-right:solid #000000 1pt;border-bottom:solid #000000 1pt;border-top:solid #000000 1pt;vertical-align:top;padding:5pt 5pt 5pt 5pt;overflow:hidden\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-left:7.086614173228355pt;margin-right:9.094488188976399pt;text-align:justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-bb471701-7fff-931b-f599-3084bd8f8299\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 102 , 102 , 102 );background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A middle-aged dwarven woman wearing a blue dress of  fine cotton, emblazoned with a mountain motif in silver thread sits behind a broad oak desk, covered in neat piles of paperwork. She rises to greet you, introducing herself as </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 102 , 102 , 102 );background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Baroness Hamilda Silverkrag</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:rgb( 102 , 102 , 102 );background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">. </span></span><br /></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><b style=\"font-weight:normal\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">When the party explains that they’re here about the notice posted, she explains about how her lads were working on excavating the family tomb, when a section of the wall broke open, and a stream of monsters poured forth, attacking the miners. They retreated to take care of the wounded. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-4b1476a0-7fff-cdd6-46b9-5b0727a931ef\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">Everything happened quite quickly, and the best description that could be obtained was that they were a bunch of “giant bugs”. Some of them sprayed sticky goop on the dwarves which burned away at their clothing (and beard!). </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">Players may make a Nature check in order to determine if they can figure out the nature of the beasts; for a DC 13 check they may recognize the creatures as various castes of </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"><b>Ankheg</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">. If they exceed DC 18 on the check, they may be familiar with the general characteristics of the castes (you can provide them with some information such as typical HP amount, AC, types of attacks, or vulnerabilities and resistances from the stat blocks). </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"><b>Baroness Hamilda</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"> emphasizes the need for a quick resolution to this problem; her father’s health is declining, and they need to finish up construction of the tomb before he is called back to the Gods. Mechanically speaking, this means that the players shouldn’t be allowed to take a long rest if they wish to fulfill the terms of the bounty. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">She won’t mention it on her own, but if queried about any hazards in the tomb, she mentions there are a number of traps in order to keep out grave robbers. She makes mention of a rune used to indicate the presence of a trap; with this knowledge any players making Investigation or Perception checks to spot the traps will do so with advantage. As well, she makes mention of the <b>o</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"><b>chre jelly</b></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"> sealed in area 3; your party doesn’t need to clear that room to fulfill the 200 gp bounty, but she’s willing to offer an extra 25 gp if the party takes care of it. If any of your party includes members of races which don’t have darkvision, she will also mention that there is no natural or artificial lighting within the tomb. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal\"><br /></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">She considers it to go without saying, but if the players inquire about “loot”, make it explicitly clear that under no circumstances are they to steal from her ancestor’s tombs. They can take anything they recover from the lair of the beasts.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some alternative player hooks could include a PC being a family friend, or even perhaps a member of the clan. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><br /></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap\">Alternatively, if your group is especially unscrupulous, you may consider having them hear rumors of the trouble in the tomb. In this case, they might be inclined to take advantage of the clan's troubles in order to loot the place. </span></p></section>"},"_id":"v075aFwm0YK70sah","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}
